name: excess item
definition: Indication that an item is incorrectly present in the data.

name: number of excess items
definition: Number of items within the data set or sample that should not have been present.

name: rate of excess items
definition: Number of excess items in the data set or sample in relation to the number of items that should have been present.

name: number of duplicate feature instances
definition: Total number of exact duplications of feature instances within the data.

name: missing item
definition: Indicator that shows a specific item is missing in the data.

name: number of missing items
definition: Count of all items that should have been in the data set or sample and are missing.

name: rate of missing items
definition: Number of missing items in the data set or sample in relation to the number of items that should have been present.

name: conceptual schema non-compliance
definition: Indication that an item is not compliant to the rules of the relevant conceptual schema.

name: conceptual schema compliance
definition: Indication that an item complies with the rules of the relevant conceptual schema.

name: number of items not compliant with the rules of the conceptual schema
definition: Count of all items in the data set that are not compliant with the rules of the conceptual schema.

name: number of invalid overlaps of surfaces
definition: Total number of erroneous overlaps within the data.

name: non-compliance rate with respect to the rules of the conceptual schema
definition: Number of items in the dataset that are not compliant with the rules of the conceptual schema in relation to the total number of these items supposed to be in the dataset.

name: compliance rate with the rules of the conceptual schema
definition: Number of items in the data set in compliance with the rules of the conceptual schema in relation to the total number of items supposed to be in the data set.

name: value domain non-conformance
definition: Indication of if an item is not in conformance with its value domain.

name: value domain conformance
definition: Indication that an item is conforming to its value domain.

name: number of items not in conformance with their value domain
definition: Count of all items in the data set that are not in conformance with their value domain.

name: value domain conformance rate
definition: Number of items in the data set that are in conformance with their value domain in relation to the total number of items in the data set.

name: value domain non-conformance rate
definition: Number of items in the data set that are not in conformance with their value domain in relation to the total number of items.

name: number of physical structure conflicts
definition: Count of all items in the data set that are stored in conflict with the physical structure of the data set.

name: physical structure conflict rate
definition: Number of items in the data set that are stored in conflict with the physical structure of the data set divided by the total number of items.

name: number of faulty point-curve connections
definition: Number of faulty point-curve connections in the dataset.

name: rate of faulty point-curve connections
definition: Number of faulty link node connections in relation to the number of link node connections in the universe of discourse.

name: number of missing connections due to undershoot
definition: Count of items in the dataset, within the parameter tolerance, that are mismatched due to undershoots.

name: number of missing connections due to overshoots
definition: Count of items in the dataset, within the parameter tolerance, that are mismatched due to overshoots.

name: number of invalid slivers
definition: Count of all items in the dataset that are invalid sliver surfaces.

name: number of invalid self-intersect errors
definition: Count of all items in the data that illegally intersect with themselves.

name: number of invalid self-overlap errors
definition: Count of all items in the data that illegally self-overlap.

name: mean value of positional uncertainties (1D, 2D and 3D)
definition: Mean value of the positional uncertainties for a set of positions where the positional uncertainties are defined as the distance between a measured position and what is accepted as the corresponding true position.

name: mean value of positional uncertainties excluding outliers (1D, 2D, 3D)
definition: For a set of points where the discrepancy does not exceed a defined threshold, the arithmetical average of discrepancies between their measured positions and what is accepted as the corresponding true positions.

name: number of positional uncertainties above a given threshold
definition:
Number of positional discrepancies above a given threshold for a set of positions.
The discrepancies are defined as the distance between a measured position and what is accepted as the corresponding true position.

name: rate of positional uncertainties above a given threshold
definition:
Number of positional discrepancies above a given threshold for a set of positions in relation to the total number of measured positions.
The discrepancies are defined as the distance between a measured position and what is accepted as the corresponding true position.

name: covariance matrix
definition: Symmetrical square matrix with variances of point discrepancies on the main diagonal and covariance between these discrepancies as off-diagonal elements.

definition: Half length of the interval defined by an upper and a lower limit, in which the true value lies with probability 50 %.

name: root mean square error
definition: Radius of a circle around a given point, in which the true value lies with probability P.

name: absolute linear error at 90 % significance level of biased vertical data (Alternative 1)
definition: Absolute vertical accuracy of the data’s coordinates, expressed in terms of linear error at 90 % probability given that a bias is present.

name: absolute linear error at 90 % significance level of biased vertical data (Alternative 2)
definition: Absolute vertical accuracy of the data’s coordinates, expressed in terms of linear error at 90 % probability given that a bias is present.

name: circular standard deviation
alias: circular standard error, Helmert’s point error, CSE
definition: Radius describing a circle, in which the true point location lies with the probability of a normal distribution at 39.4 %.

name: circular error probable
definition: Radius describing a circle, in which the true point location lies with the probability of 50 %.

name: circular error at 90 % significant level
definition: Radius describing a circle, in which the true point location lies with the probability of 90 %.

name: circular error at 95 % significance level
definition: Radius describing a circle, in which the true point location lies with the probability of 95 %.

name: circular near certainty error
definition: Radius describing a circle, in which the true point location lies with the probability of 99.8 %.

name: root mean square error of planimetry
definition: Radius of a circle around the given point, in which the true value lies with probability P.

name: absolute circular error at 90 % significance level of biased data
definition: Absolute horizontal accuracy of the data’s coordinates, expressed in terms of circular error at 90 % probability given that a bias is present.

name: absolute circular error at 90 % significance level of biased data
definition: Absolute horizontal accuracy of the data’s coordinates, expressed in terms of circular error at 90 % probability given that a bias is present.

name: uncertainty ellipse
definition: 2D ellipse with the two main axes indicating the direction and magnitude of the highest and the lowest uncertainty of a 2D point.

name: confidence ellipse
definition: 2D ellipse with the two main axes indicating the direction and magnitude of the highest and the lowest uncertainty of a 2D point.

name: relative vertical error
definition:
Evaluation of the random errors of one relief feature to another in the same dataset or on the same map/chart.
It is a function of the random errors in the two elevations with respect to a common vertical datum.

name: relative horizontal error
definition: Evaluation of the random errors in the horizontal position of one feature to another in the same dataset or on the same map/chart.

name: number of incorrectly classified features
definition: Number of incorrectly classified features.

name: misclassification rate
definition: Number of incorrectly classified features relative to the number of features that should be there.

name: misclassification matrix
definition: Matrix that indicates the number of items of class (i) classified as class (j).

name: relative misclassification matrix
definition: Matrix that indicates the number of items of class (i ) classified as class (j ) divided by the number of items of class (i ).

name: kappa coefficient
definition: Coefficient to quantify the proportion of agreement of assignments to classes by removing misclassifications.

name: number of incorrect attribute values
definition: Total number of erroneous attribute values within the relevant part of the dataset.

name: rate of correct attribute values
definition: Number of correct attribute values in relation to the total number of attribute values.

name: rate of incorrect attribute values
definition: Number of attribute values where incorrect values are assigned in relation to the total number of attribute values.

name: data product specification passed
definition: Indication that all requirements in the referred data product specification are fulfilled.

name: data product specification fail count
definition: Number of data product specification requirements that are not fulfilled by the current product/dataset.

name: data product specification pass count
definition: Number of the data product specification requirements that are fulfilled by the current product/dataset.

name: data product specification fail rate
definition: Number of the data product specification requirements that are not fulfilled by the current product/dataset in relation to the total number of data product specification requirements.

name: data product specification pass rate
definition: Number of the data product specification requirements that are fulfilled by the current product/dataset in relation to the total number of data product specification requirements.

name: physical structure conflicts
definition: Indication that items are stored in conflict with the physical structure of the dataset.

name: bias of positions (1D, 2D and 3D)
definition: Bias of the positions for a set of positions where the positional uncertainties are defined as the deviation between a measured position and what is accepted as the corresponding true position.

name: chronological disorder
definition: Indication that events is incorrectly ordered against the other events.

name: rate of geometric inconsistency
definition: Rate of items in a common area representing the same real world object with different coordinates in two different datasets according to a tolerance.

name: count of geometric fidelity failure
definition: Number of differences between registered geometry in the dataset and the actual geometry of the real world object.

name: rate of geometric fidelity failure
definition: Error rate of difference between registered geometry in the dataset and the actual geometry of the real world object.

name: complete tessellation
definition: Total number of erroneous polygons within the data.

name: user defined maintenance frequency
definition: Evaluation of acceptance quality limit, AQL for user defined maintenance frequency from a feature has changed in the real world until it is updated in the database.

name: maintenance frequency
definition: Evaluation if a dataset is maintained as set by maintenance frequency.

name: currentness
definition: Degree to which data has attributes that are of the right age in a specific context of use.

name: rate of omission for spatial coverage
definition: Percentage of reference feature geometry where data is absent.

name: rate of spatial discontinuity
definition: Quantity of spatially discontinuous data in relation to the total quantity of data.

name: rate of omission for temporal coverage
definition: Temporal duration without data in relation to the total temporal duration in which data is supposed to be present .

name: rate of imperfect coverage
definition: Percentage of data that fails to provide full coverage due to certain quality issues.

name: rate of omission for metadata
definition: Quantity of missing metadata in relation to the total quantity of metadata that are supposed to be present.

name: rate of occurrence of sensitive information
definition: Percentage of data where sensitive information is present.
